\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action clears the contained contents of the child tracks of the selected MIDI items. Used to clean up the contents of a region item if you want to change, move, or remove it.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This file contains various functions that are used by the region item actions. The other region item scripts won't run without it.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action will copy the items and automation of all child tracks underneath and within the bounds of a single selected MIDI item. It will then paste those contents to the child tracks of all pooled MIDI items, removing their previous contents.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This action will render the tracks you have selected up through all folders they are children of. It will also include sends contained in those folders in the render. You have to set up your render settings to be 'Stems (selected tracks)' for it to work properly though. Also have your render settings have the filename output as the $track wildcard.\par}
}
